Return the child Container that should be used to process this Request, based upon its characteristics. If no such child Container can be identified, return null instead.

Interface defining methods that a parent Container may implement to select a subordinate Container to process a particular Request, optionally modifying the properties of the Request to reflect the selections made. A typical Container may be associated with a single Mapper that processes all requests to that Container, or a Mapper per request protocol that allows the same Container to support multiple protocols at once.
